        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali146-kilavi">ituvumatu. itaṟkum muṉṉaṅkūṟiya uraiyaik kūṟikkoḷka.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali146">
              <l>uraicela vuyarntōṅki cērntārai yorunilaiyē</l>
              <l>varainillā viḻuma muṟīi naṭukkuraittut teṟaṉmālai</l>
              <l>yaraiciṉu maṉpiṉṟāṅ kāmam puraitīra</l>
              <l>vaṉṉameṉ cēkkaiyu ḷārā taḷittavaṉ</l>
              <l>ṟuṉṉiya kālan tuṟanta vaṇiyaḷāy</l>
              <l>nāṇu niṟaiyu muṇarkallā ṭōṇñekiḻpu</l>
              <l>pērama ruṇka ṇiṟaimalka vannīrtaṉ</l>
              <l>kūreyi ṟāṭik kuvimulaimēl vārtarat</l>
              <l>tērvaḻi niṉṟu terumaru māyiḻai</l>
              <l>kūṟupa kēḷāmō ceṉṟu; </l>
              <l rend="space">elliḻāy, eṟṟi varaintāṉai nāṇu maṟantāḷeṉ</l>
              <l>ṟuṟṟanīr pōla viṉavutir maṟṟitu</l>
              <l>kēṭṭīmi ṉellīrum vantu;</l>
              <l rend="space">vaṟanteṟa māṟṟiya vāṉamum pōlu</l>
              <l>niṟainteṉṉai māyppatōr veḷḷamum pōluñ</l>
              <l>ciṟantavaṉ tūvaṟa nīppap piṟaṅkivan</l>
              <l>teṉmē ṉilaiiya nōy; </l>
              <l rend="space">nakku nalaṉu miḻantā ḷivaḷeṉṉun</l>
              <l>takkavir pōlu miḻantileṉ maṉṉō</l>
              <l>mikkaveṉ ṉāṇu nalaṉumeṉ ṉuḷḷamu</l>
              <l>makkā lavaṉuḻai yāṅkē yoḻintaṉa</l>
              <l>vukkā ṇiḵtō  vuṭampuyirk kūṟṟākac</l>
              <l>cekkaram puḷḷit tikiri yalavaṉoṭiyā</l>
              <l>ṉakkatu paṉmā ṇiṉaintu;</l>
              <l rend="space">karaikāṇā ṉōyu ḷaḻuntā tavaṉaip</l>
              <l>puraitavak kūṟik koṭumai nuvalvīr</l>
              <l>varaipava ṉeṉṉi ṉakalā ṉavaṉait</l>
              <l>tiraitaru munnīr vaḷāka mellā</l>
              <l>niraikatir ñāyiṟṟai nāṭeṉṟēṉ yāṉu</l>
              <l>muraikēṭ puḻiyellāñ celvēṉ puraitīrntāṉ</l>
              <l>yāṇṭoḷip pāṉkollō maṟṟu;</l>
              <l rend="space">maruḷkūr piṇaipōṉ mayaṅkaven nōy ceyyu</l>
              <l>mālaiyum vantu mayaṅki yerinuti</l>
              <l>yāman talaivantaṉ ṟāyi ṉataṟkeṉṉōy</l>
              <l>pāṭuveṉ pallāruṭ ceṉṟu;</l>
              <l rend="space">yāṉuṟṟa vevva muraippiṟ palarttuyiṟṟum</l>
              <l>yāmanī tuñcalai maṉ;</l>
              <l rend="space">etirkoḷḷu ñālan tuyilārā tāṅkaṇ</l>
              <l>mutirpeṉmēṉ muṟṟiya vennō yuraippiṟ</l>
              <l>katirkaṇ maḻuṅki matiyu matirvatupō</l>
              <l>lōṭic cuḻalvatu maṉ;</l>
              <l rend="space">pērūr maṟukiṟ peruntuyiṟ cāṉṟīrē</l>
              <l>nīraic ceṟuttu niṟaivuṟa vōmpumiṉ</l>
              <l>kārtalaik koṇṭu poḻiyiṉun tīrvatu</l>
              <l>pōlāteṉ meykkaṉalu nōy;</l>
              <l rend="space">iruppiṉu neñcaṅ kaṉaluñ celiṉē</l>
              <l>varuttuṟum yākkai varuntuta lāṟṟē</l>
              <l>ṉaruppa muṭaitteṉṉu ḷevvam poruttip</l>
              <l>poṟicey puṉaipāvai pōla vaṟituyaṅkic</l>
              <l>celvēṉ viḻuma muḻantu;</l>
              <l rend="space">eṉavāṅkup pāṭa varuḷuṟṟu</l>
              <l>vaṟaṅkūr vāṉattu vaḷḷuṟaik kalamarum</l>
              <l>puḷḷiṟ katupoḻin tāṅku maṟṟuttaṉ</l>
              <l>ṉalleḻiṉ mārpaṉ muyaṅkali</l>
              <l>ṉalla ṟīrntaṉ ṟāyiḻai paṇpē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
              <l>More than a king of scorching/punishing nature, talking into trembling, making have affliction</l>
              <l>those who joined him very highly so that [their] speech would be current, without standing [still] </l>
              <l corresp="1-3c">at the limit of one state passion is devoid of love.</l>
              <l corresp="5">Being on with ornaments that abandon [her] when approached [and] departed</l>
              <l corresp="3d-4">the one who insatiably cared [for her] on a spotless bed soft [as] goose [feathers],</l>
              <l corresp="6">she perceives neither shame nor self-control. [Her] shoulders emaciated,</l>
              <l corresp="7">while a fullness [of water] well up in [her] big beautiful rain eyes, while that water</l>
              <l corresp="8">moves to [her] sharp teeth [and] flows over [her] round breasts,</l>
              <l corresp="9">as a chariot stands by the way [she] with choice jewels is in confusion.</l>
              <l corresp="10">Won’t you go [and] listen to what they say?</l>
              <l>You with bright jewels, you may ask like those who experienced [it]:</l>
              <l>“did she forget also shame about the one who cut [and] limited?”,</l>
              <l corresp="11-13">please you all come [and] listen to this:</l>
              <l>It is like the sky that is changed when scorched by drought</l>
              <l>and it is like a flood becoming full [and] hiding me,</l>
              <l>the pain that is permanent upon me,</l>
              <l corresp="14-17">coming fully so that [my] strength is severed on account of the excellent one.</l>
              <l>Smiling, it seems you are ready to say: </l>
              <l corresp="18f">“she is one who lost all beauty”. Did I not lose [it] indeed?</l>
              <l corresp="20">My shame which was much, [my] beauty and heart</l>
              <l corresp="21">stayed behind there near him at that time.</l>
              <l corresp="22">See there: as for this, while it is a prop for body [and] soul</l>
              <l corresp="24">I smile, thinking many times</l>
              <l corresp="23">about the round crab with pretty dots on the dunes.</l>
              <l>Talking much about the greatness of the one whose heart is not impressed with pain,</l>
              <l corresp="25f">he who does not see the shore, you talk cruelty.</l>
              <l corresp="27">The one to marry [me] will not part from me. Him</l>
              <l corresp="29">I said to the sun with rays in a row to search</l>
              <l corresp="28">over the wave-brining three-watered [sea and] all the earth</l>
              <l corresp="30">and I will go to all when hearing the word. He who was flawless</l>
              <l corresp="31">where will he hide?</l>
              <l>If evening too, who causes hot pain so that [I] am confused like a doe </l>
              <l>full of confusion, came with obscurity [and] flame-tipped</l>
              <l>midnight came to pass I would sing my pain</l>
              <l corresp="32-35">about that, going to many people.</l>
              <l>When talking about the troubles I had, even though you put many to sleep,</l>
              <l corresp="36-37">you certainly won’t sleep.</l>
              <l>When talking about the hot pain that matured upon me, having ripened</l>
              <l>in that place, without that the sleep of the world who receives [it] becoming full,</l>
              <l>the moon too, [its] rays becoming blunt, as if shaking</l>
              <l corresp="38-41">runs [and] whirls indeed.</l>
              <l>O worthy people with great sleep in the streets of the big village,</l>
              <l>Beware of experiencing it in full, subduing you,</l>
              <l>the pain that burns my body, unlike </l>
              <l corresp="42-45">the rainy season that, although it comes about [and] pours down, ends.</l>
              <l>Even though it is [still here], [my] heart burns. If it goes,</l>
              <l>I cannot stand the suffering of [my] body that feels suffering.</l>
              <l>It has a fortress, adapting to the trouble inside me.</l>
              <l>Becoming vainly weak like a doll, fashioned [and] made by a machine,</l>
              <l corresp="46-50">I will go, bearing affliction.</l>
              <l>While singing like that, because he </l>
              <l corresp="51+54">with a good handsome chest felt grace [and] embraced</l>
              <l>her like when for a bird, that is crazed for [want of] generous drops </l>
              <l corresp="52f">from a sky abounding in drought, those flow down,</l>
              <l corresp="55">[her] unhappiness ended. [Such] is the nature of [those with] choice jewels.</l>
            </lg>
